caption: Dante Alighieri, or Alighiero, baptized Durante di Alighiero degli Alighieri and also known only by the name of Dante, of the Alighieri family (Florence, between 14 May and 13 June 1265 – Ravenna, night between 13 and 14 September 1321) , was an Italian poet, writer and politician.
Too bad we can't get closer; with the rain and the gray weather we cannot observe the details well. I like the contrast of the white base with the dark color of Dante. statue that I really liked.
A bronze statue of Dante made in 1882 by Jean-Paul Aubé, erected due to the Italian poet's frequent visits to the first university of Paris.
